               <p>ELIZABETH POTTERTON. I am mother of 
               <persName id="t18310512-178-person1332">
                  John 
                  Bardwell Potterton
               <interp inst="t18310512-178-person1332" type="surname" value="Bardwell Potterton"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310512-178-person1332" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310512-178-person1332" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             - he will be ten years old next July. On Wednesday, the 4th of May, he left my house between six and seven o'clock in the evening, and he came back at near nine, without his cap, which he had on when he went out.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310512-178-person1333">
                  JOHN 
                  NEAL
               <interp inst="t18310512-178-person1333" type="surname" value="NEAL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310512-178-person1333" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310512-178-person1333" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Philip-lane, with my mother I am ten years of age. On the 4th of May I was out with little Potterton, in Old-street - as we were going along, the prisoner took his cap off, and ran away with it; I had not seen him before, but I am sure he is the person - I saw his face when he took off the cap; I cried Stop thief! and saw him taken.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310512-178-person1334">
                  JOHN 
                  BARDWELL POTTERTON
